	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That's right.  Okay, so that tells me that I should have the interrupt output of the mapper enabled upon reset. And even though the IRQ line will be asserted from the MMC3, the CPU is not going to recognize it until the user calls the CLI instruction. Makes sense. Thanks!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
